<subSubSection id="B918E9CC1A2ABF0E3A914929FAF87CEA" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="77C05542A41B843AFA9CDCDD2947A378" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="1181DA83F2FFA187DA2AB0AFC7E3D66F" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Body length: male 12.5-13 mm, female 14-15 mm. A large species with elongate, unconstricted abdomen. Male with wing yellowish (
<figureCitation id="165FA79920CEBD662C7A6CF17923474A" captionStart="Figures 36–47" captionStartId="F10" captionText="Figures 36 - 47. 36 - 46 Wings of Peradon species of the bidens - group: 36 P. bidens ♂ Suriname RMNH 37 P. bispina ♂ holotype 38 P. aurifascia ♂ holotype 39 P. angustiventris ♂ Suriname RMNH 40 P. angustus ♀ neotype 41 P. flavipennis ♀ holotype 42 P. normalis var. SUR- 17 B ♀ Suriname RMNH 43 P. normalis typical var. ♀ Suriname RMNH 44 P. pompiloides ♂ holotype 45 P. pompiloides ♀ paratype 46 P. niger ♂ holotype 47 Wing of P. palpator ♂ holotype (flavofascium group)" figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures36-47" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362280" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures36-47">Fig. 38</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="07713F3D6796523D7A6790F6B3C2DFA5" captionStart="Figures 129–135" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figures 129 - 135. Dorsal habitus of Peradon species (bidens group) 129 P. angustus ♀ neotype 130 P. angustiventris ♂ Suriname RMNH 131 P. angustiventris ♀ Brazil Manaus INPA 132 P. luridescens ♂ Suriname RMNH 133 P. luridescens ♀ Suriname RMNH 134 P. aurifascia ♂ Brazil CSCA 135 P. aurifascia ♀ Brazil MZUSP. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures129-135" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362293" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures129-135">134</figureCitation>
), female with wing yellow only anterobasally and with grey subapical cloud (
<figureCitation id="110B1A48652B576B56A571E518F66F40" captionStart="Figures 129–135" captionStartId="F23" captionText="Figures 129 - 135. Dorsal habitus of Peradon species (bidens group) 129 P. angustus ♀ neotype 130 P. angustiventris ♂ Suriname RMNH 131 P. angustiventris ♀ Brazil Manaus INPA 132 P. luridescens ♂ Suriname RMNH 133 P. luridescens ♀ Suriname RMNH 134 P. aurifascia ♂ Brazil CSCA 135 P. aurifascia ♀ Brazil MZUSP. Scale bar: 10 mm." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures129-135" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362293" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures129-135">Fig. 135</figureCitation>
). The abdomen is dark brown, except for a pair of yellow maculae on tergite 2. The species resembles 
<taxonomicName id="37D8A3D9C71C25C71B2218748C62C910" genus="P." lsidName="P. angustiventris" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="angustiventris">
<emphasis id="2CC880338D1AE7F2EDEDF3EC1A697DF5" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. angustiventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and especially 
<taxonomicName id="F98FAB750B65011DDDFFB271C9CEE952" genus="P." lsidName="P. luridescens" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="luridescens">
<emphasis id="794372527C24EF66135F496987F795C4" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">P. luridescens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but differs from those by the absence of a fascia of golden pile along the mesonotal transverse suture. It also differs from most other 
<taxonomicName id="0176B51CBC97D96653DE8DC5C55BEEE8" authority="Reemer, 2013" authorityName="Reemer" authorityYear="2013" class="Insecta" family="Syrphidae" genus="Peradon" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="Peradon" order="Diptera" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3566F9B7ADDAA9CBC0A0A948FFAD95FE" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Peradon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
species (except for some small species of the 
<taxonomicName id="4835734941A075F9DE70A8932FE5F6E6" lsidName="flavofascium" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" rank="species" species="flavofascium">
<emphasis id="7AA39A6093D5FF43EF5C7D10862AB139" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">flavofascium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group) in the smooth and shining bare median facial vitta (
<figureCitation id="CC50CE81536EAC35E17D67BFCD1A7367" captionStart="Figures 67–73" captionStartId="F15" captionText="Figures 67 - 73. 37 - 39 Abdomen in dorsal view 67 P. costaricensis male (holotype) 68 P. aurifascia male (Brazil CSCS) 69 P. luridescens male (Suriname RMNH) 70 Face of P. aurifascia male (holotype). Note smooth and bare median vitta 71 Tergite 4 of P. aurifascia in lateral view. Note reddish apical margin 72, 73 Scutellum: 72 P. angustiventris female (Brazil INPA) 73 P. angustus male (neotype)." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures67-73" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362285" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures67-73">Fig. 70</figureCitation>
). Male genitalia as in 
<figureCitation id="419BEBEA69CAF16BC8BFF7C8CEE1165C" captionStart="Figures 268–273" captionStartId="F46" captionText="Figures 268 - 273. Male genitalia of Peradon species 268 P. costaricensis paratype 269 P.? normalis Brazil Rondonia LACM 270 P. niger holotype 271 P. bispina holotype 272 P. pompiloides holotype 273 P. aurifascia Sao Paulo CNC." figureDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures268-273" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/362316" pageId="0" pageNumber="1" tableDoi="10.3897/zookeys.896.36493.figures268-273">Fig. 273</figureCitation>
.
</paragraph>
